<br>
Regarding song damage. DOT songs take a while, not my favorite group tactic. I don't think the math is right with below vs chords/denons. Particularly with instruments. DOTs last for three ticks, so they constantly dish out damage. I used this to drop blues at level 20. Too tired to figure the comparison. But i think DOTs dish more hurt than below.<br>
<br>
Regarding taunt. A high DD nuke will taunt very heavy. you will have a hard time getting him back.<br>
<br>
Regarding psalm of warmth. it is a 8 pt DS that stacks with mage DS. <br>
<br>
 <p><IMG ALIGN=center BORDER=0 SRC="http://www.prexus.com/harmonyofsouls/pics/sigkoi2.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaebriol.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aebriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/01 9:38:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's.  Grouping and tactics.</span><hr size=1> One very important thing to know about dot songs:<br>
<br>
They do not do dmg instantly. They do dmg after 3, 6 and 9 seconds. If you refresh the song at 8 seconds, it will do dmg at 3,6, 8+3 (11), 14, 19, 22, etc ... you will not get the full effect, so when using dot songs, twist in 4 songs, and make SURE you do not do it fast enough to have all 4 up at all times (which a good bard can when concentrating under good conditions)<br>
<br>
Aebriol <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uelloden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elloden</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/01 2:11:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's.  Grouping and tactics.</span><hr size=1> I guess I missed this one the first time (I don't swing by here too much). Prexus has a really great group of high level bards (lower levels too I'm sure but I don't know them ;) who had a lot of good comments.<br>
<br>
Just a few very general comments:<br>
<br>
Mob agro- I firmly believe that the closer you are the more likely you are to be attacked. I learned from Thalish all about this way back in the day. Back before they had evade we could control the mobs facing somewhat by getting on both sides of the mob and I would be right on it and she would be at the edge of melee range. I could give her more back stabs and when I got too hurt I'd back to the edge of melee and let it beat on her ;-) Seriously though, learn to just be on the edge of melee range if you wanna go in swinging but not get the beat down.<br>
<br>
Psalms of Cooling/Warmth- These songs do give a DS based on singer level (10 at 55 I think). These stack with any other DS but honestly don't see much use in my weave. They get broken out the most in groups with 2 bards in a few situations.<br>
<br>
Pixie Strike/Song of Twilight (SoT)- I have not used Pixie since they lowered the second resist check, but even in the bad old days it was useful for MAYBE locking 2 mobs down. It can also be very useful for locking one mob down for spawn breaking (chain mez it until you want to kill the mob to get the spawn set up right). Can also be very useful if you do not have a reliable stunner to interupt casting when fighting nasty casters.<br>
<br>
Drums vs Swords- Personally I say go with what you like. I like swinging weapons (made more attractive with breath of harmony because when wielding that sword I can add an extra song to the weave). I'd like to think I'm as useful as a bard who plays all intruments. I got great respect for the awesome job bards who whip out the drums etc do, but I just don't enjoy it as much. I've parsed my logs since level 30 or so and I think weapons and singing work pretty good. At the same know when you bust an intrument out!<br>
<br>
Know your group! If I am light on healing with a lot of melee power that is plowing through mobs then waiting on the shaman/druid before the next my focus is reduce damage, heal/mana, speed kill. If it's me, 2 clerics (yeah right, that could happen) and 3 tanks then I probably need to buff the tanks to high heaven so they can kill fast, etc.<br>
<br>
Make sure your group knows you. For example the level 55 mana song is basically unlimited sta regen, clarity2, and level 6 heal song in one. If you have a lute in inbetween battles/all the time/etc let your shaman know that they can wince for mana. If they sit at full life and OOM for half the night somethings wrong there.<br>
<br>
Learn song/spell stacking- When casting class X joins the group warn them that X won't stack/you are handling X/or you need to drop a song so thay can get X to stack with your song (casters get really annoyed when they waste mana on buffs that don't stack ;-).<br>
<br>
Now for the top 5 signs you sing the mana song too much (all in good humor, please don't take offense).<br>
<br>
5. Druid_01 tells the group, 'Hey can I get FS mace to work on 1H Blunt inbetween casting?'<br>
<br>
4. Enchanter_02 tells the group, 'I'm not casting Clarity anymore, can I pull now?'<br>
<br>
3. Mage_03 tells the group, '10 skill increases on Divination off True North in the last 5 minutes!'<br>
<br>
2. Cleric_04 tells the group, 'Nuking target now!'<br>
<br>
and last but not least....<br>
<br>
1. Warrior_05 tells the group, 'So that's what my mana bar looks like full!'<br>
<br>
