Also, there are times instruments are useful and times when they aren't.  Just gotta play around with them.  Tho, by about level 18+, boastful bellow is owned by dots on usefulness to party and damage dealth.  And it just gets worse higher level you are, I haven't touched boastful bellow in a long time.  It does like 28 dmg a nuke for me, and my dots do around 50 a tick each and stacking up 3 is no problems.<br>
<br>
As for switching instruments, I probably have the same setup you do.  Bank 4 of my hotkeys are setup like this.  1 and 2 are my melee weapons slots.  The other 8 hotkeys are just a direct mapping of my inventory.  Then I leave the instrument I am gonna swap in next on my mouse pointer as I play a song.  Then when that song plays, I stop it, start the song for the next instrument, then go to hotbank 4 and swap in the instrument as the song gets going.  It only checks the instrument right as the song plays, not when you start it or as it gets going.<br>
<br>
Dolphin Oceansinger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umikantifson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikantifson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/01 1:19:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's.  Grouping and tactics.</span><hr size=1> Thank you and thank you Dolphin!  The mouse pointer trick for instrument switching did the trick splendidly!  (But what happens when your three songs in your twist require three different instruments)?  I managed my first ever solo against blues using not but a pure song attack!<br>
<br>
But now for some more questions.<br>
<br>
Solon's Song of the Siren's.  (Charm).<br>
<br>
I worked extensively with the song and my group last night.  I am having some serious problems trying to get it to work as it's descriptions says it should.  My problem is as follows.  I would charm a MoB.  I would run it around with ease till I found a second MoB.  I would target second MoB (With charm still in effect on first MoB). and tell charmed MoB to Attack.  Well now I would have two MoBs aggroed on ME!  LOL  It seems that with the charm still playing when I targeted the second MoB it became charmed.  Thus one MoB attacking me and one MoB attacking the one attacking me.<br>
<br>
To get it to work for me it seemed that the best way was to go charm one then aggro another.  Then tell charmed MoB to Guard Me causing it to attack the other aggroed MoB.  And since I would be attacking nothing they would then fight it out till charm wore off then I would have both again till charm kicked back in.  I got this to work for me but I still think this should be more efficient.<br>
<br>
